issue.body:
for exemple:

```
var x, y = fctn (z)
```

gives us in javascript:

```
var x=self.fctn(z)[0];
var y=self.fctn(z)[1];
```

but it should be:

```
var tmp=self.fctn(z);
var x=tmp[0];
var y=tmp[1];
```

it seems that a code like this:

```
var l = []
if True
    for i in l
        console log (i)
    end
    if True -> console log "coucou"
end
```

produce the following code :

``` javascript
var l=[];
if ( true )
{
    extend.iterate(l, function(i){
        console.log(i)
    }, self)
}
else if ( true )
{
    console.log('coucou')
}
```

so when there is a for loop, the following inline condition doesn't work well

